Jesse Folds - MS  - 2017-07-23



2017-07-23
										
										I have had to use this warranty more times than I would have ever suspected. As one user stated, in the case of an AC issue...waiting for parts or the service man to contact you can seem like an eternity. Once they arrived, they called and ordered the parts and had them FedEx express overnighted. He was there first thing in the morning, sitting outside in his truck waiting for the FedEx delivery to arrive. Overall, I have been extremely satisfied with First American Warranty. Once I even looked at other warranty companies prior to renewing just to see if I could save some money, but bang for the buck....repairs, and appliances that that First American Warranty covers by default tend to be a premium upgrade with all of the other warranty companies. Unfortunately, my copay has gone up slightly every year, and I assume that is because I have actually used this warranty, but it is still a lot cheaper than paying for the complete cost out of my own pocket.
									



