Chris - PA  - 2017-07-19



2017-07-19
										
										I received HSA from the seller for free when I purchased a house.  So far I had to call them for a hot water tank issue and furnace issue.  The hot water tank after a couple visits and part replacements eventually got replaced with a bran new one.  The plumber gave great service and was prompt and I had no issues with his service or HSA\'s service.  The furnace was the same way.  It ended up being an easy fix but still the service was great on by both HSA and the repair tech.  Even if I would have paid for the HSA warranty it would have paid for itself in a few months.  I definitely recommend it for anyone buying a new house.  As for someone who is really handy or has been in their house for a while it really depends on the shape of your appliances.  The warranty is a little pricey to have everything properly covered but  it definitely helps when something unexpected happens,
									



Joseph Reyes - OH  - 2017-07-19



2017-07-19
										
										I have had nothing but the best experience with our HSA home warranty.  Buying a home is stressful enough, but having the peace of mind knowing that problems can be fixed is priceless!!

Yes, customer service can be tough to get on the phone.  It is very frustrating, but once on the phone they are professional, and very easy to deal with.  They are also very responsive in giving updates on repairs once in progress.

The website portal to start a repair is effortless, and is the easiest way to go.

We have never had an issue getting our repairs completed, or having competent individuals complete the work.  In today\'s world everyone wants their issues fixed instantaneously, but the reality is sometimes it takes time.  As long as you are cognizant that things break at the most inopportune time, and you have to take a deep breath and go through the process; you will be fine.  All of our service provider have been professional and exception in their repair process.

I will continue to renew our policy for as long as HSA will allow!!
									



