Chelsea Pollard - TX  - 2017-07-18



2017-07-18
										
										Don\'t have many people who cover my area so that\'s been a issue for me personally.  The service from landmark employees has almost always been super pleasant they are very friendly and easy to discuss issues with. 
									



Angus MacMillan - UT  - 2017-07-11



2017-07-11
										
										After having, but never using this warranty for alomst a year, I had a regrigerator and swamp cooler go out in the same week...No problem I thought, I have this home warranty the seller included in the price of the home. Unable to reach anyone by phone or email after many attempts, I finally opened an online service request. The next day I was contacted  by a refrigerator repair company telling me the soonest they could get out was a week from today. That was not acceptable so I tried calling landmark at least 5 times, waiting on hold for ever... opened up a chat window from their website..... which remained inactive for a full 45 minutes, and  sent them emails from both their website and directly with zero response. 

I did not hear from anyone except to receive an email that they had charged my credit card $60 for the fridge repair order. It was not until I threatened to give them a poor review that I got a somehwat personally directed email. To cut a long story short,  I ended up cancelling both service tickets and booked service myself with people coming out in two days vs a week. In both cases the service fees for the onsite calls were less than the $60 deductible from Landmark and both fees would credit against any repair cost.

In closing.... I am not sure that anyone actually works at Landmark other than in their WEB team. I think the company is a shell and like the Wizard of OZ with has a few  short wizards pulling knobs and dials behind a large LANDMARK HOME WARRANTY web curtain.

My advice...put $100 / month in the bank for repairs and forget about buying Landmark home warranty.

									



